{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableprotocol\/make(pollfd:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"make","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"GLibPollFDT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"pollfd","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GLibPollFDT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"title":"make(pollfd:)","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:3GIO19CancellableProtocolPAAE4make6pollfdSbqd___t4GLib14PollFDProtocolRd__lF","roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"GIO"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableProtocol\/make(pollfd:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"make","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"GLibPollFDT"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"text":"pollfd","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"GLibPollFDT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GLibPollFDT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"PollFDProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PollFDProtocolP"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When this function returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":", you should use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_cancellable_release_fd()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to free up resources allocated for the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"pollfd","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". After a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":" return, do not call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_cancellable_release_fd()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If this function returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":", either no "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"text":" was given or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"resource limits prevent this function from allocating the necessary","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"structures for polling. (On Linux, you will likely have reached","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the maximum number of file descriptors.) The suggested way to handle","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"these cases is to ignore the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You are not supposed to read from the fd yourself, just check for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"readable status. Reading to unset the readable status is done"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with "},{"code":"g_cancellable_reset()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that in the event that a [signal[Cancellable](\/\/documentation\/gio\/cancellable\/oncancelled(flags:handler:)] signal handler is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"currently running, this call will block until the handler has finished."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Calling this function from a signal handler will therefore result in a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"deadlock.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableProtocol"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a [PollFD](\/\/documentation\/glib\/pollfd corresponding to "},{"code":"cancellable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"; this can be passed","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_poll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and used to poll for cancellation. This is useful both"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for unix systems without a native poll and for portability to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"windows.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableProtocol":{"role":"symbol","title":"CancellableProtocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CancellableProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"CancellableProtocol"}],"abstract":[{"code":"GCancellable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableProtocol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableprotocol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableProtocol/make(pollfd:)":{"role":"symbol","title":"make(pollfd:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"make"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"GLibPollFDT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"pollfd"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GLibPollFDT"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableProtocol\/make(pollfd:)","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableprotocol\/make(pollfd:)","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Creates a [PollFD](\/\/documentation\/glib\/pollfd corresponding to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"text":"; this can be passed","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_poll()"},{"type":"text","text":" and used to poll for cancellation. This is useful both"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for unix systems without a native poll and for portability to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"windows."}]}}}